    "The institution of the polity also determines the physical, symbolic, and imaginary values, that are acknowledged for members of the Base.",
    "We call Ground the set of acknowledged values.",
    "An element of the Ground will be called a state.Objects of the Political Configuration are political formations (p-formations, in the sequel), and depend on the Base I, while objects of the Political Foundation are political sites (p-sites, in the sequel), and they depend on the foundational pair (I, A).",
    "PreliminariesIn what follows we assume that the Base I in the foundational pair (I, A) is a finite set.Notations 1.1.1 (i) For any finite set X, the set of all subsets of X will be denoted P(X).",
    "(ii) We put P 0 (X) ∶= P(X) ∖ {∅}."
